17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-custom max-w-none","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Cybersecurity is no longer just an IT concern — it is a board-level priority. For SaaS companies handling customer data, a single breach can destroy years of trust building. The average cost of a data breach in 2025 reached $4.88 million, according to IBM's Cost of Data Breach Report."]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Growing SaaS companies face unique challenges: rapid scaling often outpaces security controls, engineering teams prioritize shipping speed over security reviews, and limited resources mean security teams are stretched thin."]}],["$","h2","4",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"The Zero-Trust Architecture"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Zero Trust is the foundational security model for modern SaaS companies. The principle is simple: never trust, always verify. Every access request is authenticated, authorized, and encrypted regardless of where it originates."]}],["$","p","8",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["Implementation starts with identity as the new perimeter. Okta's Zero Trust framework requires every user to authenticate for every session, even inside the network. Okta Identity (rated 4.9/5) provides SSO, MFA, and lifecycle management for thousands of apps."]}],["$","h2","10",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Access Management"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Single Sign-On (SSO)"}],": Mandatory for all internal tools. SSO eliminates password fatigue and reduces phishing risk. Okta and Azure AD are the leading providers."]}],["$","p","13",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)"}],": Enforce MFA for all accounts. Hardware keys (YubiKey) provide the strongest protection, followed by authenticator apps, with SMS as a last resort."]}],["$","p","14",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["- ",["$","strong","1",{"className":"font-bold text-[#F0F4F8]","children":"Just-in-Time Access"}],": Grant temporary elevated permissions only when needed, automatically revoked after use. Tools like Teleport and Akeyless provide ephemeral infrastructure access."]}],["$","h2","16",{"className":"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight","children":"Compliance Frameworks"}],["$","h3","18",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"SOC 2 Type II"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["SOC 2 is the standard for SaaS security. It requires documented controls across five trust criteria: security, availability, processing integrity, confidentiality, and privacy. Achieving SOC 2 certification typically takes 6-12 months and costs $50,000-100,000."]}],["$","h3","21",{"className":"text-lg font-bold text-[#F0F4F8] mt-8 mb-3","children":"ISO 27001"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"text-[#8BA3BE] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-base","children":["International standard for information security management. It requires a formal ISMS (Information Security Management System). Many European customers require ISO 27001 certification."]}],"$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25"]}]
